data.text/html: Predictor Distributions (set mean/SD to match real data)

Shows ±2 SD band around the regression line to visualize spread of residuals (Variance = SD²)
Shows ±1.0 SD band. SD measures average distance of points from the line.
95% CI: Range where the TRUE regression line likely falls. Narrower with more data.
95% PI: Range where a NEW individual observation would likely fall. Always wider than CI.

data.text/markdown: Model Equation: y = 0.0 + 1.0×x + 0.5×z

Coefficient Interpretation (Two Continuous Predictors, RAOS Style)

Intercept (β₀ = 0.0): When x=0 and z=0, the predicted y is 0.0. Slope of x (β₁ = 1.0): Holding z constant, a 1-unit increase in x corresponds to a 1.0-unit higher y. z Effect (β₂ = 0.5): Holding x constant, a 1-unit increase in z corresponds to a 0.5-unit higher y. (Currently held at z=50.0 for visualization)
